data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":307,"item_id":"msg_0fb8ad7ff7bdc1ba006933b50d97a881969a0c57f46b263208","output_index":2,"content_index":0,"text":"Contoso Electronics has a detailed Whistleblower Policy that emphasizes maintaining a safe and transparent work environment for employees, contractors, and third parties. Below are key points of the policy:\n\n1. **Purpose**:\n   - Encourage employees to report unethical or illegal activities.\n   - Maintain a secure and transparent workplace.\n\n2. **Definition of Whistleblower**:\n   - An individual reporting illegal, unethical, or policy-violating activities.\n\n3. **Reporting Procedures**:\n   - Employees can report concerns immediately to:\n     - Human Resources Department.\n     - Email the Compliance Officer at **compliance@contoso.com**.\n     - Call the Compliance Hotline at **1-800-555-1212**.\n   - Reports should include detailed information such as:\n     - Time and date of the incident.\n     - Parties involved.\n     - Description of the incident.\n     - Evidence related to the incident.\n   - Anonymous reporting is available via the Compliance Hotline.\n\n4. **Protection Against Retaliation**:\n   - Retaliation against whistleblowers is strictly prohibited.\n   - Employees retaliating against whistleblowers may face disciplinary action, including termination.\n\n5. **Confidentiality**:\n   - Whistleblowers' identities will remain confidential wherever permitted by law.\n\n6. **Investigation**:\n   - All reported incidents will be promptly and thoroughly investigated.\n\nContoso appreciates and supports efforts to ensure ethical and responsible behavior to maintain a transparent and safe working environment.","logprobs":[]}

